# Source for /etc/hosts on the router (Xiaomi X3000T / OpenWrt 24.10).
# Documented in router-openwrt-x3000t.md ("SNI proxy via /etc/hosts").
# Update with:
#   python scripts/openwrt/upload.py scripts/openwrt/etc-hosts /etc/hosts
#   /etc/init.d/dnsmasq restart
#
# 45.155.204.190 is an external SNI proxy used to bypass RU blocks for the
# AI/Spotify/Telegram sites listed below (origin lost; do not assume trust).
# Twitch was REMOVED on 2026-05-12: the proxy refuses Twitch CDN, HLS gives
# 'Connection reset'. Without an override Twitch resolves via sing-box/podkop
# fake-IP and exits through the primary tunnel (awg2 / Neth since 2026-06-02).
# Spotify routing notes (2026-05-13): the user's Premium is tied to a Nigerian
# account, so any non-NG egress (FI via SNI proxy, NL via awg2, ...) trips the
# "country does not match profile" guard. We tried awg2 (Neth NL) but it
# changes nothing for that account, so Spotify was left on the SNI proxy here
# (Finland) -- same behavior as before, no need to fight the FI/NL difference.
# Spotify UNPINNED on 2026-05-20: SNI proxy 45.155.204.190 stopped responding
# (100% ICMP loss, TCP/443 timeout). With the pin in place clients just hang
# waiting for 45.155.204.190. Without the pin Spotify resolves via sing-box,
# gets fake-IP, exits through primary tunnel (awg2) -- player will probably show country
# mismatch (NG profile vs FI egress) but at least it stops hanging. The pin
# block stays here, commented out, for quick rollback once we have a working
# proxy or an NG egress.
# WARNING (2026-05-20): the SAME 45.155.204.190 is still pinned below for
# Gemini / Grok / OpenAI / Copilot / ElevenLabs / DeepL / Claude / Trae /
# Windsurf / Manus / Notion / AIStudio / Telegram / Spotify-CDN. Those will
# all start hanging too once their TCP sessions die. Either find a new SNI
# proxy IP or unpin them and route via podkop -> primary tunnel (see switch-primary-tunnel.sh).
# UNPINNED 2026-06-02: SNI proxy 45.155.204.190 dead; AI block below commented out.
# Traffic uses dnsmasq -> sing-box (podkop) -> bind_interface from podkop.main.interface.
# Restore pins only when a working SNI proxy IP is available.

